title: Lyft gets its first Wall Street buy recommendation and it's not even public yet
text: Lyft won't list on the Nasdaq until the end of March but one Montana-based investment firm is already rating it a "buy."

title: Here's why Levi Strauss, the world's biggest denim brand, is going public
text: For the first time in more than three decades, investors can buy shares of Levi Strauss & Co., the world's biggest jeans seller.

title: Lyft IPO could be '$1 billion or more' windfall for California's coffers
text: California could reap a bonanza of "$1 billion or more" in new taxes from the upcoming stock offering of ride-hailing service Lyft, according to former California State Treasurer John Chiang.

title: Elon Musk says SpaceX's first Starship test flight 'hops' are only days away
text: SpaceX founder and CEO Elon Musk said in a series of tweets on Sunday that the first very short test flights of the company's massive rocket called Starship are "hopefully" this week.

title: Fast-fashion retailers like Zara and H&M have a new threat: the $24 billion used clothes market
text: By 2028 the used-fashion market is set to skyrocket in value to $64 billion in the U.S.,while fast-fashion will only reach $44 billion.

title: Port Report: To Slow Steam Or Not Slow Steam; That Is The Latest IMO 2020 Question
text: Shippers may pay the price in less choice and lower reliability as the ocean freight industry games out the best way to operate under next year's cap on the sulfur output of marine fuel.

title: Levi Strauss IPO, Pricing Forecasts Upgraded Amid Heavy Demand
text: The forthcoming Levi Strauss IPO has been upgraded and price forecasts raised amid heavy demand.

title: 3 Reasons to Avoid the Lyft IPO
text: Here's why investors may want to hit the brakes ahead of the ride-sharing juggernaut's public-market debut.

title: SpaceX's Mars, Deep-Space Ship To Begin Key Testing Any Day Now
text: The SpaceX Starship, which is being designed for deep-space travel to places like Mars, could start so-called hop tests as early as this week, Elon Musk said.

title: Lyft, Uber can't change fact that the Silicon Valley IPO is just getting worse for public investors
text: Lyft, Slack, Pinterest and Postmates have already filed. Uber and Airbnb are expected to join before the end of the year.
